GateDocument.TextWithNodes: Preliminary CALL FOR PAPERS International Workshop on Issues and Applications of Database Technology ( IADT'98 ) http : / / www . srdc . metu . edu . tr / iadt 98 . html Berlin , Germany , July 6 - 9 , 1998 In connection with The 3 rd World Conference on Integrated Design and Process Technology Sponsored by : Society for Design and Process Science SCOPE The 3 rd World Conference on Integrated Design and Process Technology is a major international forum for the integration of design and process technologies . The workshop is organized as a part of this conference . The objective of the workshop is to provide an effective forum for the exchange of ideas , techniques , and applications among researchers and practioners from academia , business and industry working in various fields of database systems . Suggested topics include , but are not limited to , the following areas : - Process Technology - Workflow Management Systems - Novel Database Applications - Data Mining , Knowledge Discovery and Knowledge Bases - Advanced Transaction Models - Interoperable and Heterogeneous Database Systems - Information Retrieval - Deductive and Object- Oriented Database Systems - Real- Time and Active Database Systems - Scientific and Engineering Database Systems - Temporal , Spatial and Geographical Database Systems - Multimedia and Hypermedia Database Systems - Database Applications on the WWW - Databases and Programming Systems - Parallel and Distributed Database Systems - Query Processing and Optimization - Mobile Database Systems - Imprecise and Uncertain Information - View Management and Data Warehousing - Client / Server Database Systems - Database Theory and Algorithms - Distributed Object Management - Transaction Models for Object Systems - Databases for Computer- Aided Software Engineering - Intelligent User Interfaces - Document Databases - Digital Libraries IMPORTANT DATES E- mail Abstract Submission ( ASCII file ) May 30 , 1997 Full- Paper Submission ( ps file ) October 15 , 1997 Notification of Acceptance December 15 , 1997 Camera- Ready Copy Submission February 2 , 1998 PAPER SUBMISSION Authors are invited to submit the abstract of papers before May 30 , 1997 . The abstracts should not be more than 200 words . The full papers describing relevant , original and unpublished research or experience works should be emailed before October 15 , 1997 . All accepted papers will be published in the conference proceedings . Authors of selected papers will also be invited to submit an extended version of their papers either to be published in the Fall 1998 special issue of Journal of Database Management or in the book entitled "Issues of Database Technology and Design" to be published by Idea Group Publishing , USA .
